Sheesh!  OK, the official name INCLUDES the .ARPA until such time
they join an Official domain (.MIL, .dca.MIL,  .EDU,  etc).   The
policy  for  this  is  contaonted  in  one  of the DDN management
bulletins issued about 3 or 4 months ago.  (Don't  ask,  I  don't
have time to go look it up).  If they are on the ARPA side of the
house and don't  consider  themselves  bound  by  the  management
bulletins,  I'll put on my hat from the Internet Engineering Task
force and tell them they still have to do it.

Tell the host administrator to get with it and publish  his  host
name with the dotted notation when he sends mail.

Capt.  StJohns, DDN PMO et al

